Wonga, a London-based loan provider
backed by Balderton Capital and others, may offer short-term
credit in Ireland by the end of the year, the Sunday Telegraph
reported, without saying where it got the information.  The consumer finance group, advised by consulting firm
PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP, is also considering expanding into
Commonwealth countries including  Canada , the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
